Content:
Very cool discussion regarding higher-kinded programming and FP concepts in general.  One thing I don&#x27;t get is when the author writes:<p><pre><code>  Personally, I try to avoid using the word &quot;monad&quot;
  on this site and focus on the bind function
  instead, as part of a toolkit of functions for
  solving problems rather than an abstract concept.
</code></pre>
That&#x27;s pretty much the definition of &quot;monad.&quot;[1]  Why shrink from it?  Unless the author for some reason is worried that their content will be shunned due to using the proper terms for concepts being discussed.<p>1 - Yes, the existence of a bind operator is not required for satisfying the Monad laws.  Which is why I said &quot;pretty much.&quot;
